SIMPLE: incur
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incur
<hw>In*cur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Incurred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Incurring</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>incurrere</ets> to run into or toward; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in +
<ets>currere</ets> to run. See <er>Current</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To meet or fall in with, as something inconvenient,
harmful, or onerous; to put one's self in the way of; to expose one's
self to; to become liable or subject to; to bring down upon one's self;
to encounter; to contract; <as>as, to <ex>incur</ex> debt, danger,
displeasure, penalty, responsibility, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know not what I shall <qex>incur</qex> to pass it,⟦br⟧
Having no warrant.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To render liable or subject to; to occasion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest you <qex>incur</qex> me much more damage in my fame than you
have done me pleasure in preserving my life.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incur</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Incur
<hw>In*cur"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass; to enter.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Light is discerned by itself because by itself it
<qex>incurs</qex> into the eye.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incurability</ent>⟦br⟧
